		<table width=85% border=0 cellpadding=5 cellspacing=0 align=center>
  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF MIGHTY STRIKE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;54</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;10 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;54 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline all landed attacks will automatically be either Critical Hits or Crippling Blows.  This discipline lasts for 10 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>HMM </span><b>, By Thorwald</b><br><br>
<p>Hate to post and sound like I am just making accusations but half the people posting here don't seem to know a whole lot about the potential for a skill like this, or how to take advantage of it.<br>
<br>
 Landing All crits/crips for ten seconds is simply awesome POTENTIALLY.<br>
<br>
The POTENTIAL for doing awesome amounts of damage here depends on how often you land your attacks, and is therefore influenced by the damage the weapon you use
vs. the amount of times you will get a swing (and therefore a chance at hitting the mob) within the next ten seconds.<br>
<br>
If you use this skill against a high RED mob you will have almost no chance of doing great amounts of damage at all. By the same token any mob that you hit readily could take a hell of a lot of damage. Several posters mention doing up to 2k damage in ten
seconds. pretty awesome stuff.<br>
<br>
Therefore use this skill against mobs that you are successfully hitting to start with.<br>
Then use the best pair of Damage delay weapons you can get your hands on or whatever combo you normally use that does the most damage in the least amount of time. This will give your character the best chance of effectively damaging the opponent when using this skill.<br>
<br>
MAX Damage:<br>
If you try and figure the damage based on max damage you are somewhat deluding yourself anyway. Many warriors in this game think if they can hit once in a day for 300 points of damage it makes them some sort of Uber Tank. Don't let your ego
interfere with your effectiveness. And lets not enhance the Warriors reputation for being
stupid (which is already quite prodigious)<br>
<br>
Note on Exe Axe Weighted Axe and Others:<br>
Try not to use anything 2handed or 1handed with a delay over 40..you will just hurt yourself<br>
<br>
Silly Side benefit: If you don't know how high you can crit things for with different weapons nice way to find
out..<br>
<br>
<br>
I like this Discipline ...<br>
<br>
<br>
</p>
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>NICE!</span><b>, By Koolmoodi</b><br><br>This discipline is the bomb, get a cleric to complete heal you when you go berzerk, use the discipline with a BIG damage weapon with a haste, exe blade is one of best if you have good haste,you will do extreme damage.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>IT WOULD SEEM TO ME</span><b>, By Nallatikie nomanna</b><br><br>That if you were at haste cap, and strength cap, you couldnt gain any benefit from being beserk.  If this is true, then using this in this situation would wield the same results as letting yourself fall below 35% health. It would be true that whatever weapon that you use that does the most damage normally would be wise to use with this discipline. Although I have not seen this in use personally, the prospect of scoring crippling/criticals with every blow is immense.  Bringing down 25-35% health of a mob in 10 seconds is really quite helpful in any situation.  Too bad on the refresh time.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>WEIGHTED AXE</span><b>, By Bugguluk</b><br><br>The best idea with this discipline would be to whip out your Weighted Axe first, get 1 huge hit in, then start dual weilding.  I do this in normal fights (without the dis) and it is very effective.  So you would (potentially) get a big 400ish damage hit in, then a whole lot of 150ish hits with your faster weapons.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>CHAMPION OF XEGONY</span><b>, By Blain </b><br><br>Well, I was in Karnors last night doing the hand/warlord room.I leveled to 54 and instructed the cleric to let me go beserk on a tough mob. I'm using Wurmslayer main hand and I was doing crits for 160 -190 all night before the discpline use. I went beserk, activated the Mightystrike on a Bodyguard and my best crip was 299 (308 actual damage dealt). One thing you had better trust your cleric. <br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
